145105.name: HepB3 (% of one-year-olds immunized)
145105.description: Hepatitis B is a viral infection that attacks the liver and can cause both acute and chronic disease.

display.name: Share of one-year-olds vaccinated against hepatitis B (HepB3)

source.name: World Health Organization (WHO); UNICEF
source.additionalInfo:
Vaccination coverage rates are sourced from the WHO/UNICEF's Estimates of National Immunization Coverage (WUENIC). Available at: https://www.who.int/immunization/monitoring_surveillance/data/en/

The number of children unvaccinated is calculated by Our World in Data using WHO/UNICEF coverage rates, and UN Population Division (2019 Revision) population estimates for the relevant age group. Available at: https://population.un.org/wpp/
